      "blockIndex": 6,
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Why does WAF matter? Because NAND cells have limited P/E (Program/Erase) cycles. If WAF is 3x, your 600 TBW rated drive effectively only lasts 200 TBW of your data. Two factors dominate WAF:",
